In a skillet, cook sausage, celery, onion and green pepper until sausage is no longer pink and vegetables are tender; drain. stir in soup, milk, pimientos, rice, poultry seasoning and salt. Pour into an ungreased 1-1/2-qt. baking dish. Cover and bake at 350 degrees F for 50 minutes, stirring occasionally. Combine bread crumbs and butter; sprinkle on top. Bake, uncovered, 20 minutes more.